desc: Start about eight feet left of Dirty Girl, et al below an arête. This is about 25 feet left of the start of Tutti Fruiti.    Face climb up just right of the arête, following several short, vertical cracks. At the top, move right (finger sized cam as a directional) to the La Lagartua anchor.

name: Rasguna Las Piedras
desc: Short climb ends unders a roof

name: Rasca
desc: Climb up the crack via some slabby moves and good fingerlocks. Get to the vertical section and pull through. You should reach an anchor here. If you want to continue climbing break out right and build your anchors here.    I haven´t climbed the second or third pitch.

name: Viaje Magico
desc: The roof is the crux

name: Guanestone
desc: Try to avoid using the prow on the right if you want to keep the grade at 6c.

name: Pompis and Circumstance
desc: Start in the same spot as El Imperio de los Sentidos (route #48 in the 2016 topos), near a dihedral with a wide flake/crack.     Climb the easy dihedral to an obvious tree on a ledge.

name: Under Wire Brah
desc: On the far side of the via ferrata, you'll see the power line overhead that runs from the canyon rim down into the valley below the cliffs. This climb starts almost directly below the power line at a right facing corner (the corner is the line of 57 Anos).     The trail along the base of the cliff ascends to the corner (there's a fixed hand line) and then descends.    Move right from the corner and climb the black face past three bolts to the communal fixed anchor.

name: Animalejo
desc: Decent climbing at first untill you have to pull over the roof. Prepare for small holds and hard beta. The second half is very sandy and bolts are spaced out. I never found a proper anchor. I had to lower on only one locking carabiner.

name: Preludio
desc: Climb to a roof and pull it

name: El Dinamico
desc: Starts with El Duo but then splits after first pitch. Bouldery

name: La Arenosa
desc: Boulder up to the ledge, extend draw or solo to next bolt. Follow slab moves up a poop ramp to scary corner. Once you get to the corner reach right To a blind jug. Ascend sketchy rock corner and pull with all of your might on a flake that shivers with anticipation. Hooray anchors!

name: Erase Una Ve Un Piton
desc: Pitch one    Climb up suspect rock. If you´re lucky it won´t fall off. Follow this up a dirty crack and finally break left when you hit a roof. Trend left to hit the anchors.    Pitch two    Climb up the choss corner and then break left around the blind corner to jungling. There should be two bolts in this route but I wasn´t able to find them. Hit the anchors and rap down.

name: La directa del darien
desc: Adventure line, the last pitch is chossy and exposed, just horrid.

name: El que no baile tiene pecueca
desc: Nice face climb

name: Chile
desc: Hard roof to pull at the start followed by easy climbing.

name: Tu o yo
desc: Starts on the left side then climbs the arete and a small roof.

name: Mujer salvaje
desc: If you like bouldering, you will be served.

name: La alfombra negra(Project)
desc: This is an unsent project

name: El vikingo arrecho
desc: Very good climbing with a few cruxes. You will find a few rests.

name: El silencio de los inocentes
desc: A few roofs plus a traverse right.

name: PROYECTO(Project)
desc: Project - no sent yet

name: El plom
desc: Traverse overhang to the left

name: La era del burro
desc: First small roof at 1/3 then second roof at 2/3 of the route. Right after the second roof, follow the line of bolts that goes straight up. This is where the 5.12b starts.

name: El gecko volador
desc: Short and bouldery.

name: La Bruja De Blair
desc: Short powerful moves to a roof at the top.

name: Zion
desc: Climbs hard to read rock at first then the anchor is just below the roof.

name: Subete la pata
desc: Beautiful orange face climb.

name: No todos losperros van al cielo
desc: The easiest of the harder routes.

name: Chimborazo
desc: This is a shared start to three routes. This one goes right and you need trad gear for the second half. Can be top roped after climbing one of the other two versions.

name: La gorgona
desc: Trad gear needed to climb a nice crack system.

name: El acrobareto
desc: One of the hardest route in La Reserva. Climbs the arete to the overhang.

name: Legalize it don't criticize it
desc: Shares the start of "Orion" but goes right after the first couple of bolts.

name: El lord gales
desc: Beautiful and challenging line. At the end of the traverse, follow the bolts on the right.

name: Ya what
desc: Good dihedral climbing but justy too short.

name: Welcome to Mojarra
desc: Can be linked in one long pitch. 70 meter rope needed.

name: No me diga que no, si si
desc: Two roofy sections. The top half climbs on dark rock.

name: Pun pun polvora
desc: Negociate an overhang/roof section than finish on a more vertical climb.

name: Cous cous
desc: Like many routes at La Mojarra, a few roofs to negociate.

name: De gerber para una princesa
desc: This is a direct start to Gerber. The crux is definitely pulling the cave.

name: Aqui no hay princesas
desc: Amongst the hardest routes in La Mojarra.

name: Mana Macona
desc: Shares the start of "Animals 5.10b", turns right into the roof and shares the anchor of "El acrobata 5.11d".

name: La espinita
desc: Go straight up then vear to the right to get up the giant cave roof.

name: Los sapos contra atacan
desc: This is an extension of "A ultima hora 5.11d".It climbs the overhang that goes to the "Fuego en la proa" anchor.

name: Mas platon y menos prozac
desc: Really good climbing but just a bit harder than the classic 10b.

name: Fuckemon
desc: What? Another roof to start the route!

name: Rastman
desc: Like most lines at sector 2, this is a face climb.

name: La replica
desc: This is a shared start to three routes. At the end of the overhang, you will see two lines of bolts. Take the one on the left.

name: Esta Temblando on Santander
desc: Pulls roof to the left then straight then head right to the top.

name: Idiotas tecnológicos
desc: ZONA III

name: Espolon Chupeton
desc: Hardest route on the wall

name: El dedo del camello
desc: Short second pitch after climbing "Portal Rolo". There are two lines of bolts above "Portal Rolo". This is the version that goes right.

name: Magic chuch
desc: Not as good as the other two 5.12b at this sector.

name: David y goliat
desc: Shared start then climbs the dihedral.

name: El perro andulaz (Project)
desc: Project - not sent yet

name: El cielo perruno (Project)
desc: Project - not yet sent

name: Twisted sister
desc: First small roof at 1/3 then second roof at 2/3 of the route. Right after the second roof, follow the line of bolts on the right to avoid the harder 12b finish.

name: Fixer se partio
desc: Get established on the arete, make a few moves to a ledge. A few more moves will bring you to the anchor.

name: No es malpaso ni dificil
desc: Easiest route of this sector.

name: Los renglones torcidos de Dios
desc: ZONA III

name: Torrente
desc: Full trad line that climbs a big roof.

name: Ganjedi(Project)
desc: Second pitch project

name: El cabro
desc: Second pitch above "De renga en renga 5.12c".

name: La variante (Project)
desc: Project - not sent yet

name: La vuelta al mundo (Project)
desc: Project - not sent yet

name: The rolling stone
desc: Hardest line at this sector.

name: Cuando los sapos atacan
desc: This is an extension of "A ultima hora 5.11d".The bolts are hard to see on the extension.

name: Hammer
desc: Roof at the bottom, roof at the top separated by a long face climb.

name: Diestra y siniestra
desc: Two 5.11c lines that ends at the same anchor. This one is on the right.

name: La vaca loca
desc: Face climb followed by a small roof.

name: Ojo al gorila
desc: At mid height, the line traverses right before it goes back up again.

name: Don cangrejo(Project)
desc: Big overhang project

name: La suite del 12ª
desc: ZONA III

name: Los poetas del face
desc: Longest route and one of the best of this sector.

name: A Su Abuela
desc: Start on A Su Hermana but then head left at the roof and end at the chains for La Capanita

name: Lallana
desc: Short route with strong roof

name: Orquideograma
desc: The route is probably accessible by climbing part of the 5.10a to the right and walk left to the start of the trad line.If anybody has better beta for this route, please post it.

name: Sal al te
desc: ZONA III

name: Ganjadawan
desc: Varied climbing including a seem, horizontal crack, overhang and a few jugs.

name: Retroevoluccion
desc: One of the longest single pitch in La Mojarra

name: Faltas no me sobran
desc: Another 5.13a at this sector.

name: El ultimo proton
desc: I don't know if it is worth documenting this route since it is probably never climbed. A fully trad line going 100% horizontal. Need to climb a second pitch project to get to it...

name: Mini
desc: Same start as for La rasca 12c but turns right for a slightly harder version.

name: La Mojarra mecanica
desc: Two 5.11c lines that ends at the same anchor. This one is on the left.

name: De renga en renga
desc: Climbs on the darker section of rock.

name: El aji
desc: You first have to climb "La pepitoria  then this second easier pitch.a

name: 5.12 RX
desc: Really long route. Too bad this is not fully bolted.

name: La custodia
desc: Short route with severe overhang. Some great feature but too bad to route is not all bolted.

name: Alice in wonderland
desc: Need a few pros for the last section of the route.

name: Todo gozque es prenador
desc: Similar to "Al ' hora" in grade and style.

name: Al 'hora
desc: First half is overhanging and second is more of a face climb.

name: Oscar
desc: Although the same grade, this is a slightly harder version of Brostidarks.

name: A burro viejo
desc: Short second pitch after climbing "Portal Rolo". There are two lines of bolts above "Portal Rolo". This is the version that goes left following the arete.

name: Legado musica
desc: Short trad line.

name: Simiosis
desc: Project - not sent yet.

name: Cadena perpetua(Project)
desc: Project. Last line on the left.

name: Jack custodio
desc: Only fully sport route at this sector.

name: Plan chamanico
desc: Sandy rock at the bottom followed by an overhang then a roof, then a little face climb to another roof. The finish is easier.

name: La Primera
desc: A variation on El Duo that veers left and can be done in one pitch.

name: El click
desc: Very short overhang climb.

name: Griptonita
desc: Shares the start of El plom 5.10d but goes right about mid-height for a harder but shorter finish.

name: El abrazo de la gorda
desc: Short and easy trad line.

name: El 9 de richy
desc: Climb the blunt arete, then a finish with a few jugs and a few not so good holds.

name: Entre canibales
desc: Another route with 2 roofs to climb.

name: La guarderia
desc: One of the hardest lines in La Mojarra.

name: El marciano
desc: The route angles right at mid height.

name: Central pasajera
desc: Sport route.

name: El pelon
desc: Trad route.

name: La momia cotra caca
desc: Second hardest at this sector.

name: Prosopopeyate
desc: Not a classic but worth doing.

name: El hombre duplicado
desc: You need gear for the first half then it is protected with bolts.

name: Kundalini
desc: Starts with a roof down low then the arete. Great exposure!

name: Cipres
desc: Short and bouldery.

name: Senor pequeno
desc: Bouldery start to get to the ledge. Easier climbing will bring you to the heartbreaking crux at the end.

name: Todo al Revers
location: Parque Nacional Natural Los Nevados  Nevado Del Ruiz
desc: Easy 5.8 dihedral up to a ledge. From there go strait up a lay back crack and then into some face holds. The 5.9+ rating comes from this section after the ledge.

name: Aniversario
desc: Nice route, with variable grips, small to medium. The firts movement is the crux.

name: Alcatraz
desc: Diagonal crack without protections, if you like to climb this route are needed small stoppers and camalots from 0.5 to 5. It route is very exposed.
Classic crack.

name: La abeja jah
desc: Be careful, there might be bees at the bottom.

name: Sharaz village
desc: Hardest route at La Reserva. A good one.

name: One love
desc: Good climbing and medium height.

name: Dreadlocks
desc: Just a little longer than two two 5.11a to the left but harder.

name: Babylon
desc: Another short one not too hard.

name: Armagedon
desc: Shortest route of the crag.

name: Africa
desc: The line goes right and then left after the two roofs.

name: Reggae nice
desc: Much shorter than its neighboring three 5.12's but it is still good climbing.

name: La utopia ganjafarai
desc: One of the longest routes in La Reserva.

name: Bananei
desc: One of the longest routes in La Reserva.

name: Un plon para el sol
desc: One of the longest route in La Reserva. Good climbing.

name: Porro
desc: Mixed route that requires only one or two pros.

name: Asgard
desc: Mixte route.

name: El hermitano
desc: Short thin face climb.
Climbs the face left of the arete.

name: El precalentado
desc: Easiest route of La Reserva.

name: El catre
desc: Trad line.

name: Uniendo fuerzas
desc: Trad route.

name: La palma
desc: Mixed line.

name: Poliamor
desc: First three quarter needs gear.

name: Jah garden
desc: Best line of the sector and also the longest one.

name: Rasta doggy
desc: Climbs a left diagonal to a shared anchor.

name: Rasta girl
desc: This route climbs diagonally to the right to a shared anchor.

name: Rastamandita
desc: Slightly overhang face climb.

name: Rastafarai
desc: Pull the bulge, an easy vertical section, a roof and one more vertical section.

name: Rasta boy
desc: After pulling the first bulge, traverse left for about 10 feet and negociate two roofs.

name: Cada cuervo con su mazorca
desc: The hardest of the three moderate routes on this small wall.
